definition.value: The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of 4-chlorocinnamic acid.
The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of 3-methylcinnamic acid.
The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of 3-nitrocinnamic acid.
A polythiophene polymer, composed of poly(alkoxythiophene) macromolecules.
The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of 3-[2-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl]propanoic acid.
A poly(alkoxythiophene) polymer, composed of poly(3-alkoxythiophene) macromolecules.
A poly(3-alkoxythiophene) polymer, composed of poly(3-methoxythiophene) macromolecules.
A poly(3-alkoxythiophene) polymer, composed of poly(3-ethoxythiophene) macromolecules.
A homopolymer, composed of poly(ethyl ethoxyethylene phosphate) macromolecules.
An ionic polymer, composed of polycationic macromolecules.
A homopolymer, composed of polyalkenylene macromolecules.
A polyalkenylene polymer, composed of polybutadiene macromolecules.
One of a class of 14-membered macrocyclic diterpenoids characterised by the presence of an isopropyl group at C-1 and by three symmetrically disposed methyl groups at C-4, -8 and -12.
An EC 4.2.1.* (hydro-lyases) inhibitor that interferes with the action of tryptophan synthase (EC 4.2.1.20).
A 14-membered macrocyclic diterpene carrying an isopropyl group at C-1 and three symmetrically disposed methyl groups at C-4, -8 and -12.
Any fatty acid containing nitrogen as either a substituent or a replacement for a methylene carbon.
Any  nitrogen-containing fatty acid that is a fatty acid in which nitrogen replaces carbon as the divalent group -NH for the group -CH2 or a single trivalent N atom for the group -CH.
Any fatty acid carrying at least one halo substituent.
Any halo fatty acid containing at least one fluoro substituent.
A benzoic acid carrying a trifluoromethyl substituent at the 2-position.
A benzoic acid carrying a trifluoromethyl substituent at the 3-position.
A benzoic acid carrying a 4-trifluoromethyl substituent.
A benzoic acid carrying trifluoromethyl substituents at the 2- and 5-positions.
A bromobenzoic acid carrying a single bromo subsituent at the 4-position.
An organobromine compound comprising hexanoic acid having a bromo substituent at the 6-position.
An organochlorine compound comprising pentanoic acid with a 5-chloro substituent.
An organofluorine compound consisting of acetic acid carrying a 2-(2,2,2-trifluoroethoxy) substituent.
A member of the class of (trifluoromethyl)benzenes consisting of trans-cinnamic acid having a trifluoromethyl substituent at the ortho-position.
A member of the class of   (trifluoromethyl)benzenes consisting of trans-cinnamic acid having a trifluoromethyl substituent at the meta-position.
A member of the class of  (trifluoromethyl)benzenes consisting of trans-cinnamic acid having a trifluoromethyl substituent at the para-position.
A C-nitro compound comprising trans-cinnamic acid having a nitro group at position 3 on the phenyl ring.
A monocarboxylic acid comprising propionic acid having a 2-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl group at the 3-position.
A polybutadiene polymer, composed of poly(vinylethylene) macromolecules.
A polybutadiene polymer, composed of poly(1,3-butadiene) macromolecules.
A homopolymer, composed of polybenzoxazole macromolecules.
A polybenzoxazole polymer, composed of poly[(6,6'-bibenzoxazole)-2,2'-diyl-1,4-phenylene] macromolecules.
A homopolymer, composed of polythiourethane macromolecules.
A homopolymer, composed of poly(selenophene-2,5-diyl) macromolecules.
Any benzoic acid carrying at least one bromo substituent on the benzene ring.
An acyl chloride consisting of benzoyl chloride having a chloro substituent in the para-position.
An aroyl group formed by removing the OH from the carboxy group of 4-chlorobenzoic acid.
An aroyl group formed by removing the OH from the carboxy group of 2-chlorobenzoic acid.
An acyl chloride consisting of benzoyl chloride having a chloro substituent in the ortho-position.
An inorganic sodium salt having silicate as the counterion.
An organophosphate oxoanion which is obtained from all-trans-decaprenyl diphosphate by removal of the three protons from the diphosphate group. The major species at pH 7.3.
A phosphatidylglycerol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both linoleoyl.
A phosphatidylglycerol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both tetradecanoyl (myristoyl).
